		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Magician Guide</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:gengar@cgocable.net">Yadin</a> | 
		            5/12/1999 2:06:59 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Ok, here's the scoop.  If you have decided to choose to be a magician, you must realize a few things, first of all, you can only wear cloth, secondly, only daggers and staffs will be your weapons, and your main defence/offence option is your spells.  After going to your guild, I reccomend putting 2 points in piercing for now, one in evoke, and abjuration, then pick a skill on your own.  Once you have gained a level or two, and some well needed cash, start buying Malachite (can be found at a Gem merchant).  Buy these because you need them for summoning your pets at level 4.  They are then your best defence, and best cash grabber because they can be set to attack baddies on their own.  I suggest using the Earth Elementalkin or Fire, because the earth is the strongest in Defence, and the fire is the strongest hitter.  THis is as far as I can take you, currently my character Yadin is a level 7 magician, I will fill you in when the time is right.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
