	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hmmmm.  Read through these posts and there seems to be a bit of mis-information.  As far as applying bonus points to stats at character generation, I would recommend putting most into INT and the reaminder into STA and/or DEX.  INT is good for the mana, obviously, but STA is not primarily for HP, but it affects how fast you regen your mana.  DEX is also very important; at higher levels you will need to cast while getting beat on by a mob - the higher your DEX, the more likely you can recover from a hit while casting.  AGI is also a good stat for a mag.  This stat improves your AC somewhat, lessening the frequency of mob hits, as well as improving your foot speed.  Bottom-line:  Don't put your points into WIS unless you really want to focus on crafts ( since WIS dictates chances of success with trade skills), or STR.  All other stats are viable and applicable to a magician.  And don't fret if you don't choose optimally when generating your character.  You will be able to modify your stats accordingly by what equipment to wear at higher levels.<BR>
<BR>
Now, regarding pets... all pets are good for different situations.  From levels 4 to 23 I used the water pet 90% of the time.  Why?  Good damage and good durability.  Earth will root, but this isn't critical until higher levels.  Using the water pet while soloing will also help you develop good grouping skills.  No one want a caster over-nuking in a critical battle as it sucks the mana right out of the clerics when that mana is better served healing the tanks.  From level 24 - 35, I primarily used the Earth pets when soloing.  Why?  Because the root becomes VERY important when the mobs start hitting for 100hp a round.  When using the earth pet, I would typically alternate a DD spell with Renew Summoning to help the pet's longevity.  Also, ALWAYS cast your best fire shield on the earth pet - this is very important and can sometimes be the differencr between life and death!  When grouping with folks who want to snare/fear mobs, I recommend fire as it will inflict the most damage; the pet's HP are irrelevant when the mob is feared and pet's typically won't get hit much when grouped with a tank anyways.  If there is no fear/kiting being done, Air is the best group pet for the stuns.  The stuns will save the tanks HP and, thusly, the healer's mana, reducing downtime for the group.  Well, that's my two cents.  I hope it has been helpful.  Oh, 1 more thing.  When group with your pet, be sure to setup a hotkey with /assist on the first command line, and /pet attack on the second command line.  This will make everyone in the group happier, especially enchanters!  Also, when in dungeons, do a /pet guard here BEHIND the group.  This will help keep your pet from aggro-ing on mobs without direction.<BR>
<BR>
Be safe, fellow magicians, and good hunting!<BR>
<BR>
Rielu<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

